        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Leviticus 8</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-15-2" n="15" prev="ADub.III.73.003.007.trl.xml#line-15-1" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">‘Take Aaron and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            his sons with him, and the garments, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            anointing oil, and a calf of the sin offering, and two
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            rams, and a basket of unleavened bread.</l>
                        <l n="3">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            assemble all the congregation to the door of the tent of meeting.’</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="4">And Moses did as the Lord commanded him, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="168v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            the congregation was gathered to the door of the tent of meeting.</l>
                        <l n="5">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            And Moses said to the congregation, ‘This is the word which the Lord commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            to do.’</l>
                        <l n="6">And Moses brought Aaron and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            his sons, and <seg type="commented" n="#seg001" />commanded them to wash
                            their bodies<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref
                                target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor" /> with water.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="7">And he put on him the shirt,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            and tied him with the girdle, and clothed him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            with the robe, and put the ephod on him, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            he tied him with the embroidered |band| of the ephod, and put on the
                            ephod on him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            with it.</l>
                        <l n="8">And he put on him the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            breastplate, and he put in the breastplate the Urim and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            Thummim.</l>
                        <l n="9">And he put the turban on his head,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            and he put on the turban, on its
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            front, diadem of the holy crown, as
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="10">And Moses took the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            anointing oil and anointed the tabernacle and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            all that was in it, and consecrated them.</l>
                        <l n="11">And he sprinkled
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            some of it on the altar seven times and anointed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            the altar and all its vessels, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            basin and its place, to consecrate them.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="12">And he <supplied reason="lost">poured</supplied><ref target="#fn2"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> some of the anointing oil on Aaron’s head,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and anointed him, to consecrate him.</l>
                        <l n="13">
                            <milestone unit="page" n="169r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            And Moses brought forward Aaron’s sons, and put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            shirts on them, and tied them with girdles, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            put high caps on them, as the Lord commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            Moses.</l>
                        <l n="14">And he brought forward the calf of the sin offering,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            and Aaron and his sons reached their hands out over the head
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            of the calf of the sin offering.</l>
                        <l n="15">And he slaughtered it and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            took some of the blood and put it on the horns of the altar
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            all around with his finger and sprinkled the altar
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            and poured the blood at the base of the altar, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            he consecrated it, to ask for atonement for it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                        <l n="16">And he took all the fat that was on the stomach,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            and the extra |fat| of the liver, and the two
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            kidneys, and their fat, and Moses burned it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            on the altar.</l>
                        <l n="17">But the calf, and its skin,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and its flesh, and its dung, he burned
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            in fire outside the camp, as the Lord commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            Moses.</l>
                        <l n="18">And he brought forward the ram
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            of the burnt offering, and Aaron and his sons reached out their hands
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            over the head of the ram.</l>
                        <l n="19">And he slaughtered it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            and Moses sprinkled the blood on the altar
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            all around.</l>
                        <l n="20">And he cut the ram into pieces
                            <milestone unit="page" n="169v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            according to its pieces, and Moses burned the head and the pieces
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and the neck<ref target="#fn3" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="21">And he washed the entrails
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and the knees with water, and Moses burned the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            whole ram on the altar. It is a burnt sacrifice for a pleasing aroma,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            an offering by fire to the Lord, as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="22">And he brought forward the other ram, the ram of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            ordination, and Aaron and his sons reached out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            their hands over the head of the ram.</l>
                        <l n="23">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            he slaughtered it, and Moses took some of the blood of it and put it on
                            the soft place
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            of Aaron’s right ear, and on the thumb
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            of his right hand, and on the great toe
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            of his right foot.</l>
                        <l n="24">And he brought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            Aaron’s sons forward, and Moses put some of the blood
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            on the soft place of their right ears and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            on the thumbs of their right hands and on the great toes
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            of their right feet. And Moses sprinkled
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            the blood on the altar all around.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="25">And he took the fat, and the |fat| tail,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            and all the fat that was on the stomach, and the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            extra |fat| of the liver, and the two kidneys,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and their fat, and the right thigh.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="170r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="26">And from the basket of unleavened bread that was before the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            he took one unleavened cake, and a cake of oiled bread, and one flan,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and put them on the fat and on the right thigh.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="27">And he put all on Aaron’s hands,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            and on his sons’ hands,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            and waved<ref target="#fn4" type="noteAnchor" /> them for a wave
                            offering before the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="28">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            And Moses took them from off their hands, and burned
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            them on the altar on the burnt offering: they were an ordination |offering|,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            a pleasing aroma, an offering by fire to the Lord.</l>
                        <l n="29">And Moses took
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            the breast, and elevated it for a wave offering before
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the Lord. It became Moses’s portion of the ram of ordination,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            as the Lord commanded Moses.</l>
                        <l n="30">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            Moses took some of the anointing oil and of the blood which was on the altar,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            and sprinkled it on Aaron, on his garments,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and on his sons, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            on his sons’ garments with him, and consecrated
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            Aaron, his garments, and his sons,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and his sons’ garments with him.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="31">And Moses said to Aaron and to his sons,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            ‘Boil the flesh at the door of the tent of meeting,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            and eat it there, and the bread that is
                            <milestone unit="page" n="170v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            in the basket of ordination, as I commanded, saying, “Aaron
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and his sons shall eat it.”</l>
                        <l n="32">And you shall burn that which remains
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            of the flesh and of the bread in fire.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="33">And you shall not go out of the door of the tent of meeting for seven
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            days, until the day of completion of the days of your ordination, because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            he will fill your hand for seven days.</l>
                        <l n="34">. As he has done
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            this day, so the Lord has commanded to do,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            to ask for atonement for seven days for you.</l>
                        <l n="35">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            you shall sit at the door of the tent of meeting day and night
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            seven days, and you shall keep the charge of the Lord, so that you do
                            not die,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            for so I am commanded.’</l>
                        <l n="36">And Aaron and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            his sons did all the things that the Lord commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            by the prophecy of Moses.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote">Interpretative translation.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote">K: <emph>put</emph>; a scribal
                            error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote">K: Possibly a mistranslation, cf. Heb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">הַפָּדֶר </foreign>
                            ‘the fat’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote">Lit. ‘reached out’.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
